I noticed weed patches dying by the end of the same day that I applied it. I did have some dead grass due to using it in higher temperatures, but once the weeds were gone, I gently raked those areas and have been giving them extra water, and the green in coming back. I think that the bottle could be better designed. Its not very ergonomic. Overall, I am very satisfied with the results of Image Southern Lawn Weed Killer, and plan to make it part of my fall and spring lawn care routine.

review_text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] Ive previously treated my lawn with weed and feed granules right before spring. There were still some dandelions (and a few other weeds) that managed to survive and I felt like they were somehow still spreading. This Image Lawn Weed and Crabgrass Killer did the trick getting the remaining survivors and the ones that seems to be creeping over from my neighbors yard. I have to wait for a day that did not exceed 90 degrees to apply the weed killer, which was a challenge in the rising summer temperatures here in Georgia. Its important to read ALL of the instructions on the bottle because there is a lot to pay attention to. Theres no need for a spreader with this stray bottle, which was a big plus for me. I simply connected the bottle to a hose and let the sprayer do most of the work. I now have a weed-free lawn with no annoying dandelions threatening to take over the grass!

product_name: Image Kills Nutsedge Ready-to-Spray
review_text: Reading these comments I wonder, how many people complaining actually read the ENTIRE instructions before using. I have not tried this yet but plan on it in the next week on my centipede lawn. I have St Augustine Centipede as well and the instructions clearly say not to use it in the winter to control winter weeds on St Augustine Centipede. It also says the lawn should be established and it may cause yellowing of grass as it kills the weeds. People expect miracles, they think herbicide should kill only the weed not harm the grass any way shape or form and instructions do not say that. I certainly hope my grass is not killed and I do not want it yellowing but it is small price to pay if it kills the weeds. I do not want a lawn full of stickers that is for sure so we will see what happens.

product_name: IMAGE Lawn Weed & Crabgrass Killer Concentrate
review_text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] My yard is filled with weeds so it took me some time to decide where would be the best place to try this out. I decided to spray it along the side of my yard, between mine and my neighbors property line. We have a well and septic system, so I wanted the chemicals to be far from that. This bottle simply screws into your house and you slide a plastic piece to turn it on straight water or to mix it in. I had mine on the water option at first and didnt realize it for a few minutes when I thought it was taking too long for the level in the bottle to decrease. Ha! Then, I noticed where it said "mix". After that, I sprayed for about 5 minutes until the bottle was empty. An hour later, I walked by the area and noticed changes. Some of the weeds were wilted, but the most common sign of working were the yellowing of weeds. Product does have a strong scent, so if that would bother you, wear an N95. I tried not to inhale as much when spraying, or breathed away from the area. Overall, great product and works fast. Im very happy to have had this to try out on my weed-ridden yard!

product_name: IMAGE Lawn Weed & Crabgrass Killer Ready-To-Spray
review_text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] I have a bermuda grass lawn and Ive used Image before. The actual formula Im not sure is any different than what Ive used in the past. The dispenser is much better and easier to turn on and off. Instead of a knob where I have to awkwardly turn it and Im never sure which way to turn it. This new one is just a slider switch on the top which is extremely convenient and properly labeled so there is no question about which direction to slide it to turn it off/on. The application itself is quite easy. Just attach it to the house, turn it on and start spraying. Im never really sure how much I need to spray for it to have an affect so I just did a light layer around the lawn. It would be nice if it was dyed so I could see where I sprayed and the darkness of the grass tells me how much I sprayed. It was easy enough but one bottle was not enough for my entire lawn. I live on about 0.25 acres so its not very big but I think two bottles would be more than enough. So after the application, the waiting began. It did not happen very quickly and quite honestly, I think its gonna take more time. Some of the weeds have started to turn brown a little bit where they look unhealthy but Im not sure if theyre actually dying or not? Its been about a week now so this stuff works kind of slow. If its anything like the old stuff, itll probably take about 3 weeks. The roundup stuff my neighbor uses seems to work a lot faster. It hasnt killed my current grass yet.

review_title: Product is decent but new design bottle is horrible!
review_text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] I used this product for the insipid dollarweed that encroaches on my yard and it works great. Within a day the dollarweed started turning yellow. However the new bottle design is not very good.. I personally wished I had saved one of the older product bottles to use. Now back to the product itself. The trick with this product is mixing it and applying it at the correct rate. I used 6 oz Image for 2 gal water to treat 1,000 sf. The flowers on my clover died within a few days and the dollar weed started yellowing in the same amount of time. I have two areas that still have clover flowers, so I must not have sprayed it enough. I previously treated a 2,200 sf area with granular Weed Stop without success but Image applied 2-3 weeks later had a better outcome. Its definitely all within the mixing of the product if its mixed correctly you will see a better outcome. All in all I was pleased with the results.

review_title: Kills pretty much all the nasty weeds in your yard.
review_text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] First off I dont really know the technical names of most of the weeds out there, I just know they are weeds and dont belong in my yard. I have the typical dandelions and assorted other type weeds over running my otherwise clean yard. I waited for a nice stretch of sunny weather and sprayed the yard pretty good with the Image weed killer. One good thing is it seems like the coverage is pretty good as I think I only used a little more than half a bottle. After a few days it appears most of the weeds are dead or dying. After a week or so it looks like I have a few persistent straglers. Dont know if I missed them or they are resistant so I will try spraying again with the remaining mixture. Overall it seems to have worked pretty good.
